Hamadruas is a genus of lynx spider family Oxyopidae with Indo-Malayan distribution.

== List of species ==
Hamadruas austera (Thorell, 1894)  Singapore
Hamadruas heterosticta (Pocock, 1897)  Sulawesi, Moluccas
Hamadruas hieroglyphica (Thorell, 1887)  Myanmar
Hamadruas insulana (Thorell, 1891)  Nicobar Islands
Hamadruas pupulus (Thorell, 1890)  Nias Islands
Hamadruas severa (Thorell, 1895)  Myanmar, Lombok
Hamadruas signifera (Doleschall, 1859)  Java
Hamadruas sikkimensis (Tikader, 1970)  India, China
Hamadruas superba (Thorell, 1887)  Myanmar, Thailand, Borneo

